<HEADLINE>
FT  18 APR 94 / Mexico trade deficit up sharply
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAMIAN FRASER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MEXICO CITY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mexico's trade deficit deteriorated sharply to Dollars 1.53bn in February,
an increase of 24 per cent over the same period last year. The unexpectedly
high deficit may put additional pressure on the peso, which is already
trading at the limit against the dollar allowed by the central bank. The
February deficit was pushed up by a 19 per cent increase in imports, which
reached Dollars 6.02bn in February. Exports rose to Dollars 4.49bn, a 17 per
cent increase. Manufacturing exports jumped by 26 per cent. The government
sought to blame the growth in imports on buoyant exports in its latest
explanation of why the trade deficit is a healthy phenomenon. The government
said some 40 per cent of the imports in February will be used to make goods
that that will soon be exported.
</TEXT>
