<HEADLINE>
FT  16 APR 94 / London Stock Exchange: Equity Futures and Options Trading
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOEL KIBAZO
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Stock index futures closed firmly ahead as hopes of a reduction in UK
interest rates returned to the market, writes Joel Kibazo.
The June contract on the FT-SE 100 closed at 3,187 after reasonable turnover
of 15,792 lots. Thursday's close was 3,133 after volume of 14,698 contracts.
However, it was a poor day in the FT-SE mid-250 with only 16 lots dealt as
it closed at 3,825.
Turnover in the traded options was 44,669 contracts of which 20,172 was in
the FT-SE 100 option and Lasmo was the busiest stock option with a total of
2,833 lots.
