<HEADLINE>
FT  16 APR 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The pepper market has been rather inactive of late in the absence of buying
interest from grinder, reports Man Producten. Consequently white pepper
prices have come under increased selling pressure. In comparison with a
fortnight ago prices have declined by about 4 to 5 per cent and are now
about USDollars 2,700 a tonne, cif, for April/May shipmment and Dollars
2,600, cif, for July/August (ex-new crop). Black pepper prices, in contrast,
remained steady, though here too demand remained below normal. However, most
origins showed little or no interest in reducing prices . Black pepper grade
1 was offered this week at Dollars 1,600-Dollars 1,650 a tonne, cif.
