<HEADLINE>
FT  16 APR 94 / International Company News: Eisner tops US pay table
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN DICKSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Michael Eisner, chairman of Walt Disney, topped the US executive pay league
in 1993 with earnings of Dollars 203m  - not far short of the company's net
income, which fell 63 per cent in the year to Dollars 299.8m, according to a
survey published yesterday by Businessweek magazine. It was the highest
annual compensation for an executive anywhere in the world.
However, some Dollars 202.3m of Mr Eisner's compensation stemmed from the
exercise of stock options dating back to 1984. His salary was only Dollars
750,000 and he received no bonus as Disney's earnings fell. He is regarded
as having done an excellent job for shareholders, lifting Disney's
capitalisation from Dollars 2.2bn to almost Dollars 23bn over the past
decade.
The second highest paid executive was Mr Sanford Weill, chairman of
Travelers, the financial services group, who received Dollars 52.8m, all but
Dollars 4.3m through the exercise of stock options. Third was Mr Joseph Hyde
of Autozone with Dollars 32.2m.
</TEXT>
