international taxation standards, and it would use all possible avenues to
oppose it. 'In this matter Ciba-Geigy has the full support of the Swiss
authorities,' it said. Last week Japanese tax authorities agreed to
reimburse AIU, the US insurance company, for some of the back taxes
collected under the transfer pricing tax rules following discussions with US
tax officials.
