FT  16 APR 94 / World News in Brief: Skating Champion John Curry dies
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Former Olympic ice figure skating champion John Curry died of an
Aids-related illness. He was 44. He won the gold medal in the 1976 Winter
Olympics at Innsbruck, where his style revolutionised the sport. Curry's
innovative use of classical ballet and acrobatics heralded a new generation
of skating stars, including fellow British Olympic champions Robin Cousins,
Christopher Dean and Jayne Torvill.
