<DATELINE>
   STOCKHOLM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Pharmacia, the Swedish pharmaceuticals group, yesterday scotched rumours of
a possible delay in its privatisation, saying the industry ministry had
given the go-ahead for the sale of the state's 46 per cent holding in June.
The move could raise as much as SKr14bn (Dollars 1.8bn), making it Sweden's
biggest privatisation. Around half the shares are expected to be offered to
foreign institutions.
